On October 12, 2010, the President signed several laws, including the "Combat Methamphetamine Enhancement Act of 2010" which requires retail sellers of certain products to submit a self-certification to the Department of Justice. The "Indian Veterans Housing Opportunity Act of 2010" makes changes to Native American housing assistance programs. The authority of the Vietnam Veterans Memorial Fund, Inc. to construct a visitor center in Washington, D.C. was extended. The "Redundancy Elimination and Enhanced Performance for Preparedness Grants Act" requires FEMA to submit reports to Congress on eliminating redundant reporting requirements and assessing program performance. The "Law Enforcement Officers Safety Act Improvements Act of 2010" allows certain law enforcement officers to be exempt from state laws prohibiting concealed weapons. Lastly, the "Secure and Responsible Drug Disposal Act of 2010" provides authority for the disposal of controlled substances.